thread.title: Google quarterly profit beats expectations

title: Google quarterly profit beats expectations
text:
Google quarterly profit beats expectations 
Sky News Friday 23rd October, 2015 
Google shares have leapt after the internet colossus reported quarterly earnings that beat Wall Street expectations.Newly formed parent company Alphabet reported on Thursday that Google profit in the recently ended quarter jumped 45 per cent to $US3.98 billion ($A5.52 billion) on revenue that was up 13 per cent to $US18.67 billion.Shares were up more than 10 per cent at $US719 in after-market trades.The third quarter results 'show the strength of Google's business, particularly in mobile search', chief financial officer Ruth Porat said.'With six products now having more than one billion users ...
